00:02:07.120 --> 00:02:11.630 align:middle line:10%
This is probably-- an
electromagnetic pulse event

00:02:11.630 --> 00:02:15.010 align:middle line:10%
is perhaps our greatest
national security threat today.

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:18.030 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: Explain
what that is, an EMP.

00:02:18.030 --> 00:02:22.120 align:middle line:10%
>>MALOOF: An EMP is-- an
electromagnetic pulse--

00:02:22.120 --> 00:02:29.930 align:middle line:10%
is high intensity particles
which can flare off and come

00:02:29.930 --> 00:02:34.780 align:middle line:10%
at such a rapid rate of speed
and at such an acceleration

00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:38.190 align:middle line:10%
that they interfere
with our magnetic poles,

00:02:38.190 --> 00:02:40.470 align:middle line:10%
with our North Pole.

00:02:40.470 --> 00:02:43.090 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence,
it also, because they're

00:02:43.090 --> 00:02:46.700 align:middle line:84%
so powerful and
highly charged, they

00:02:46.700 --> 00:02:50.350 align:middle line:84%
can wipe out any
unprotected electronics.

00:02:50.350 --> 00:02:52.840 align:middle line:84%
That would include
our grid, which

00:02:52.840 --> 00:02:54.450 align:middle line:90%
is highly vulnerable already.

00:02:54.450 --> 00:02:57.280 align:middle line:84%
We put so much
demand on that grid

00:02:57.280 --> 00:03:01.050 align:middle line:84%
today that it's
basically on overload.

00:03:01.050 --> 00:03:04.150 align:middle line:84%
We upgrade it, but in
doing that, we're not--

00:03:04.150 --> 00:03:06.530 align:middle line:84%
it's basically a
jerry-rigged system.

00:03:06.530 --> 00:03:10.440 align:middle line:84%
And in addition to that, our
electronics, our electronics,

00:03:10.440 --> 00:03:14.780 align:middle line:84%
our microchips have become much
more sophisticated, much more

00:03:14.780 --> 00:03:15.710 align:middle line:90%
delicate.

00:03:15.710 --> 00:03:19.040 align:middle line:84%
And as a consequence,
such a pulse

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:23.430 align:middle line:84%
can absolutely knock
out that electronics.

00:03:23.430 --> 00:03:31.630 align:middle line:84%
Automated control systems, from
running the gas pump to ATMs.

00:03:31.630 --> 00:03:33.930 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:03:33.930 --> 00:03:36.170 align:middle line:84%
The automatic systems
for our pipelines.

00:03:36.170 --> 00:03:39.060 align:middle line:84%
We have more than a million
miles of pipelines, oil and gas

00:03:39.060 --> 00:03:41.260 align:middle line:90%
pipelines.

00:03:41.260 --> 00:03:47.550 align:middle line:84%
An EMP can trigger
those automatic systems

00:03:47.550 --> 00:03:51.260 align:middle line:84%
so that it builds up pressure
from the natural gas,

00:03:51.260 --> 00:03:52.300 align:middle line:90%
can cause explosions.

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:56.330 align:middle line:84%
There's actually been instances
of that in isolated cases.

00:03:56.330 --> 00:03:57.230 align:middle line:90%
Oil pipelines.

00:03:57.230 --> 00:03:58.690 align:middle line:90%
Fires can develop.

00:03:58.690 --> 00:04:00.740 align:middle line:84%
But if this were to
happen with an EMP event

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:04.380 align:middle line:84%
from a flare or a high
altitude nuclear explosion,

00:04:04.380 --> 00:04:08.442 align:middle line:84%
it would cover a far
greater geographical area.

00:04:08.442 --> 00:04:09.900 align:middle line:84%
Half the country,
the full country,

00:04:09.900 --> 00:04:13.030 align:middle line:84%
depending upon how
severe the EMP was.

00:04:13.030 --> 00:04:17.089 align:middle line:84%
And it could take months,
years to come back on.

00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:19.420 align:middle line:84%
By then, we will
have had affected

00:04:19.420 --> 00:04:21.506 align:middle line:90%
about 90% of the US population--

00:04:21.506 --> 00:04:22.089 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: Dead.

00:04:22.089 --> 00:04:22.990 align:middle line:90%
>>MALOOF: Dead.

00:04:22.990 --> 00:04:24.050 align:middle line:90%
From starvation--

00:04:24.050 --> 00:04:24.800 align:middle line:90%
>>NOORY: No water.

00:04:24.800 --> 00:04:25.758 align:middle line:90%
>>MALOOF: From disease.

00:04:25.758 --> 00:04:26.710 align:middle line:90%
No water.

00:04:26.710 --> 00:04:28.250 align:middle line:90%
Medical reasons.

00:04:28.250 --> 00:04:31.510 align:middle line:84%
And your urban centers could
be wiped out as a consequence.

00:04:31.510 --> 00:04:33.190 align:middle line:84%
>>NOORY: And we have
seen historically

00:04:33.190 --> 00:04:35.450 align:middle line:84%
